        %article#speakers
          %h2 Speakers

          %section.left
            %img{src: 'images/speaker/drnic.png'}
            %p.title VP of Developer Evangelism at Engine Yard 
            %p.name Dr Nic Williams 
            %p
              Dr Nic is a developer’s developer. He writes blog posts for developers; creates tools, libraries and text editor extensions for developers; and speaks to developers at conferences.
            %p 
              He’s the VP of Developer Evangelism at Engine Yard, the leading Platform as a Service. He has contributed to over 250 open source projects. He is known for creating or curating projects such as Rails Installer, Composite Primary Keys, Choc Top, App Scrolls, Rails TextMate bundle, New Gem, Tab Tab, GitHub Badges, Install Theme for Rails, and Dr Nic’s Magic Models.

          %br{style: "clear: both"}

          %section.left
            %img{src: 'images/speaker/steveklabnik.png'}
            %p.title &nbsp; 
            %p.name Steve Klabnik 
            %p
              Ruby, anarchism, critical code studies. I love hypermedia APIs and teach awesome Ruby and Rails classes with Jumpstart Lab.

          %br{style: "clear: both"}/

          %section.left
            %img{src: 'images/speaker/josevalim.png'}
            %p.title Lead Developer at Plataformatec 
            %p.name José Valim
            %p
              José Valim is a Rails Core member and author of Crafting Rails Applications. Also, he is the lead-developer of Plataformatec, a Ruby on Rails consultancy firm based in Brazil. He created and maintains many open source projects, the latest being Elixir and Dynamo, a language and web framework targeting the Erlang VM.

          %br{style: "clear: both"}/

          %section.left
            %p.title &nbsp;
            %p.name Charles Olivier Nutter
            %p
              Charles works on JRuby and other language implementations at Red Hat, helping to bring languages to the power of the JVM and bring the JVM to the broader polyglot world.

          %br{style: "clear: both"}/

          %section.left
            %img{src: 'images/speaker/brianford.png'}
            %p.title &nbsp;
            %p.name Brian Ford
            %p
              Brian has been working on Rubinius since December 2006 and with Engine Yard since January 2008. He created the RubySpec project to improve the standards for high quality, compliant Ruby implementations. He hopes to see Ruby become an even more widely used language and improved to make lives of developers even better. He also enjoys whisky but will accept a good wine in a pinch.

          %section.left
            %img{src: 'images/speaker/andrzejkrzywda.jpg'}
            %p.title &nbsp;
            %p.name Andrzej Krzywda
            %p
              Ruby and Coffee programmer. The founder of Arkency and GameBoxed. Rails teacher at University of Wroclaw.
            %p
              He's originally a backend developer, with Rails experience since 2004. He knows all the pains and beauty of Rails. Now, after working for the last 2 years on frontends, he knows how to build them properly. He will teach us all the lessons he's learned and he's going to show a lot of production frontend code.

          %br{style: "clear: both"}/

